Author-Name: Matthew A. Turner 
Title: Cost Benefit Analyses versus Referenda 
Abstract:
 We consider a planner who chooses between two public policies and ask
 whether a referendum or a cost benefit analysis leads to higher welfare.
 We find that a referendum leads to higher welfare than a cost benefit
 analysis in a "common value" environment. Cost benefit analysis is better
 in a "private value" environment. (c) 2010 by The University of Chicago. All rights reserved. 
