Author-Name: Grant Miller 
Author-Name: B. Piedad Urdinola 
Title: Cyclicality, Mortality, and the Value of Time: The Case of Coffee Price Fluctuations and Child Survival in Colombia 
Abstract:
 Recent studies demonstrate procyclical mortality in wealthy countries, but
 there are reasons to expect a countercyclical relationship in developing
 nations. We investigate how child survival in Colombia responds to
 fluctuations in world arabica coffee prices and document starkly
 procyclical child deaths. In studying this result's behavioral
 underpinnings, we highlight that (1) the leading determinants of child
 health are inexpensive but require considerable time, and (2) as the value
 of time declines with falling coffee prices, so does the relative price of
 health. We find a variety of direct evidence consistent with the primacy
 of time in child health production. (c) 2010 by The University of Chicago. All rights reserved. 
